com.helger.jcodemodel

Class JDefinedClass

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.helger.jcodemodel.AbstractJType
      • com.helger.jcodemodel.AbstractJClass
        • com.helger.jcodemodel.AbstractJClassContainer<JDefinedClass>
          • com.helger.jcodemodel.JDefinedClass
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IJAnnotatable, IJClassContainer<JDefinedClass>, IJDeclaration, IJDocCommentable, IJGenerable, IJGenerifiable, IJOwned
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    JAnonymousClass

    public class JDefinedClass
extends AbstractJClassContainer<JDefinedClass>
implements IJDeclaration, IJGenerifiable, IJAnnotatable, IJDocCommentable
    A generated Java class/interface/enum/....

    This class models a declaration, and since a declaration can be always used as a reference, it inherits AbstractJClass.

    Where to go from here?

    You'd want to generate fields and methods on a class. See method(int, AbstractJType, String) and field(int, AbstractJType, String).
